OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780589464
OL,3,CWelsh Government ministers accused of
OL,4,Cclash of views in first FMQs
OL,6,FThe interim Labour leader Ken Skates
OL,7,Ftried to highlight another difference:
OL,8,Fover new nuclear power. Plaid Cymru as
OL,9,Fa party is opposed to the development
OL,10,Fof new nuclear powers, but individuals
OL,11,Fhave been allowed to support such
OL,12,Fdevelopments in areas where there has
OL,13,Fpreviously been a plant, such as Wylfa
OL,14,Fon Anglesey, which is in the First
OL,15,FMinister's constituency.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780589464
OL,3,CWelsh Government ministers accused of
OL,4,Cclash of views in first FMQs
OL,6,FMr Skates asked him: "Do you agree
OL,7,Fthat, alongside renewables, the
OL,8,Fbuilding of as many as eight small
OL,9,Fmodular reactors at Wylfa offers
OL,10,Fenormous opportunity to provide energy
OL,11,Fsecurity, lower bills, and 8,000 jobs,
OL,12,F3,000 of which will be in your
OL,13,Fconstituency?"
OL,15,FThe First Minister did not rise to the
OL,16,Fbait, saying, "Yes, I have, on a
OL,17,Fpersonal level, always taken the
OL,18,Fapproach of fighting for the economic
OL,19,Fbenefits that come to that particular
OL,20,Fpart of Wales from that development,
OL,21,Fwhich is a reserved matter."
OL,26,@nD@VOUuD@NO]xD@OOU}D@\O]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780589464
OL,3,CWelsh Government ministers accused of
OL,4,Cclash of views in first FMQs
OL,6,F"Reserved" matters refer to decision-
OL,7,Fmaking power which lies with the UK
OL,8,FGovernment at Westminster, not the
OL,9,FWelsh Government in Cardiff.
OL,26,@nD@AOUnD@JO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G9/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780589464
OL,3,CWelsh Government ministers accused of
OL,4,Cclash of views in first FMQs
OL,6,FFurther pressed by the Labour leader,
OL,7,FMr ap Iorwerth said, "My position on
OL,8,FWylfa is very, very clear. This is a
OL,9,Freserved matter, and the manifesto
OL,10,Fcoming into this election said that
OL,11,Fthere were matters that were reserved,
OL,12,Fwhich absolutely includes Wylfa. We
OL,13,Fwill work positively on that
OL,14,Fparticular plan because of the
OL,15,Feconomic benefits locally that control
OL,16,Fflow from it and across the wider
OL,17,Fregion, plus on the elements of
OL,18,Fenvironmental positives associated
OL,19,Fwith it."
OL,26,@oD@VOU{D@IO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G10/14
