PN,46711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780589464
OL,3,CWelsh Government ministers accused of
OL,4,Cclash of views in first FMQs
OL,6,FThe third apparent contradiction was
OL,7,Fhighlighted by the Conservative
OL,8,Fleader, Darren Millar who challenged
OL,9,Fthe First Minister about road building.
OL,11,FReferring to recent closures of the
OL,12,FMenai Bridge, Rhun ap Iorwerth said
OL,13,Fthat "work within government" has been
OL,14,Fto "ensure short-term measures" and is
OL,15,Flooking at longer-term solutions.
OL,17,FBut Mr Millar said that when Plaid
OL,18,FCymru was in opposition, it supported
OL,19,Fmoves that blocked road building.
OL,26,@uD@FOUuD@]O]vD@DOUvD@_O]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G11/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46712
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780589464
OL,3,CWelsh Government ministers accused of
OL,4,Cclash of views in first FMQs
OL,6,FHe said that, "You had an opportunity
OL,7,Fevery time you did a budget deal and a
OL,8,Flegislation deal with the previous
OL,9,FWelsh government, you could have
OL,10,Factually brought forward some
OL,11,Fsolutions and put some money in the
OL,12,Ftin in order to get this project on
OL,13,Fthe go, but you didn't, did you?
OL,14,FBecause it wasn't one of your
OL,15,Fpriorities.
OL,26,@nD@OOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G12/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46713
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780589464
OL,3,CWelsh Government ministers accused of
OL,4,Cclash of views in first FMQs
OL,6,F"Instead, you and the Plaid Cymru MSs
OL,7,Fat that time voted against major
OL,8,Finvestment in our roads infrastructure
OL,9,Facross the country, not just in North
OL,10,FWales, but also, of course, on the M4
OL,11,Fcorridor in the south as well."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@_O]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G13/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46714
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780589464
OL,3,CWelsh Government ministers accused of
OL,4,Cclash of views in first FMQs
OL,6,FIn response, the First Minister agreed
OL,7,Fthat, "money was wasted, I must say,
OL,8,Fin getting to a place when nothing has
OL,9,Fhappened in recent years, and this
OL,10,Fgovernment is already doing the work
OL,11,Fto identify the solutions that will be
OL,12,Feffective and economically and
OL,13,Fenvironmentally responsible in order
OL,14,Fthat we can deliver long-term benefits
OL,15,Fsocially and economically for the
OL,16,Fpeople of, yes, the South East of
OL,17,FWales and the Brynglas areas, but we
OL,18,Fknow that it's much wider than that
OL,19,Ftoo."
OL,26,@oD@GOU{D@EO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G14/14
